{
  "texts": [
    "As part of DPCollection, we manually reassign 46-65% of dataset licences (depending on the platform), resulting in much higher coverage, thus giving risk-averse developers more confidence and breadth in their dataset use.",
    "Incorrectly specified licences.",
    "Table 2 shows that correct licences are frequently more restrictive than the ones by assigned by aggregators.",
    "GitHub, Hugging Face and Papers with Code each label licence use cases too permissively in 29%, 27% and 16% of cases, respectively.",
    "Our inspection suggests this is due to contributors on these platforms often mistaking licences attached to code in GitHub repositories for licences attached to data."
  ]
}